Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
moveMacroInsideModule(25.10)                      moveMacroInsideModule(25.10)

Name
       moveMacroInsideModule - Moves all hard macros that belong to the speci-
       fied module into its boundary

Syntax
       moveMacroInsideModule

       [-help]

       {-hInst {hinstName(s)} | -all}

       Moves  all  hard  macros  that  belong to the specified module into its
       boundary. You use this command after the module is placed in  the  core
       area.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each moveMacroInsideModule parameter.  For  a  de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command: man moveMacroInsideModule.

       -all   Moves all hard macros that belong to hierarchical modules.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -hInst {<hinstName>}
              Specifies  the  name  of  the hierarchical instance. You can use
              wildcards (*?) with this parameter.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
       The following command moves all hard macros that belong to modules that
       have hierarchical instance names that match DTMF_INST/*_TEST_INST  into
       its boundary:

       moveMacroInsideModule -hInst DTMF_INST/*_TEST_INST

